<subSubSection id="25F9656DFF8A9D7BDCADFA85FB82F8B8" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8A9D7BDCADFA85FC1CFAF8" blockId="6.[151,1437,1311,2019]" box="[201,974,1311,1336]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8A9D7BDCADFA85FE88FAF7" bold="true" box="[201,346,1311,1336]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Description.</emphasis>
Body length 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDD96FA85FDC7FAF8" box="[498,533,1311,1335]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="6.4">6.4</number>
–8.0 mm; forebody length 
<quantity id="AA1B9B03FF8A9D7BDF24FA85FC18FAF8" box="[832,970,1311,1335]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.7" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8A9D7BDCADFAD9FBC0FAB0" blockId="6.[151,1437,1311,2019]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8A9D7BDCADFAD9FED1FA94" box="[201,259,1347,1371]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Male</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="F5D82A63FF8A9D7BDD06FAD9FE64FA94" box="[354,438,1347,1371]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 30" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1219,1242]" captionTargetBox="[159,1417,200,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 30. Nazeris megalobus sp. n. 25 — habitus; 26 — male sternite VII; 27 — male sternite VIII; 28 — aedeagus, in dorsal view; 29 — aedeagus, in lateral view; 30 — aedeagus, in ventral view. Scale bars: a = 1 mm, b = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208750/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDDFDFAD9FE64FA94" box="[409,438,1347,1371]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark brown, with labrum, coxae and basal two antennal segments reddish brown, the remaining antennal segments, maxillary palpi and legs except for coxae yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8A9D7BDCADFA11FE85F9C0" blockId="6.[151,1437,1311,2019]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Head longer than wide (length/width = 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDEE6FA11FD65FA6C" box="[642,695,1419,1443]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="1.07">1.07</number>
); postocular portion 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDFFAFA11FC1DFA6C" box="[926,975,1419,1443]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="1.76">1.76</number>
times as long as eye length; with umbilicate punctation coarse and dense. Antennae slender; relative length (width) of each antennomere from I to XI as 45.0 (11.0): 15.0 (8.0): 35.0 (
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDD91FA49FDC8FA24" box="[501,538,1491,1515]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="5.5">5.5</number>
): 26.0 (
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDE19FA49FD70FA24" box="[637,674,1491,1515]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="5.5">5.5</number>
): 24.0 (
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDF61FA49FCF8FA24" box="[773,810,1491,1515]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="5.5">5.5</number>
): 24.0 (
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDFE9FA49FC60FA24" box="[909,946,1491,1515]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="5.5">5.5</number>
): 23.0 (
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BD871FA49FBE8FA24" box="[1045,1082,1491,1515]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="5.5">5.5</number>
): 21.0 (5.0): 19.0 (5.0): 16.0 (6.0): 19.0 (
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDD47FA6DFE98F9C0" box="[291,330,1527,1551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="6.5">6.5</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8A9D7BDCADF986FCDBF9B4" blockId="6.[151,1437,1311,2019]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Pronotum longer than wide (length/width = 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDEDDF981FD3FF9FC" box="[697,749,1563,1587]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="1.21">1.21</number>
), narrower than (pronotum/head = 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BD813F981FB78F9FC" box="[1143,1194,1563,1587]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="0.9">0.90</number>
) and as long as head; prosternum with strong longitudinal median carina extending to anterior margin. Elytra as long as wide, shorter than (elytra/pronotum = 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDDCDF9F9FE09F9B4" box="[425,475,1635,1659]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="0.83">0.83</number>
) and as wide as pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8A9D7BDCADF91DFBBAF89C" blockId="6.[151,1437,1311,2019]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Abdomen elongate, tergites lacking microsculpture. Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="F5D82A63FF8A9D7BDFD3F91DFBD9F950" box="[951,1035,1671,1695]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 30" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1219,1242]" captionTargetBox="[159,1417,200,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 30. Nazeris megalobus sp. n. 25 — habitus; 26 — male sternite VII; 27 — male sternite VIII; 28 — aedeagus, in dorsal view; 29 — aedeagus, in lateral view; 30 — aedeagus, in ventral view. Scale bars: a = 1 mm, b = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208750/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDF8AF91DFBD9F950" box="[1006,1035,1671,1695]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin semi-circularly emarginated at middle, area anterior emargination slightly depressed. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="F5D82A63FF8A9D7BD8F3F931FB39F90C" box="[1175,1259,1707,1731]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 30" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1219,1242]" captionTargetBox="[159,1417,200,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 30. Nazeris megalobus sp. n. 25 — habitus; 26 — male sternite VII; 27 — male sternite VIII; 28 — aedeagus, in dorsal view; 29 — aedeagus, in lateral view; 30 — aedeagus, in ventral view. Scale bars: a = 1 mm, b = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208750/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BD8AAF931FB39F90C" box="[1230,1259,1707,1731]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin V-shaped concaved at middle. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="F5D82A63FF8A9D7BDEA3F955FC9CF928" box="[711,846,1743,1767]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 30" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1219,1242]" captionTargetBox="[159,1417,200,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 30. Nazeris megalobus sp. n. 25 — habitus; 26 — male sternite VII; 27 — male sternite VIII; 28 — aedeagus, in dorsal view; 29 — aedeagus, in lateral view; 30 — aedeagus, in ventral view. Scale bars: a = 1 mm, b = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208750/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Figs. 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8A9D7BDF63F955FC9CF928" box="[775,846,1743,1767]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="29.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="28.0">28–30</number>
</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized; median lobe narrow, broadly constricted at apical third in dorsal or ventral view, with narrowly round apex, lacking laminae on dorsal side; dorsolateral apophysis broad, distinctly widened near middle, slightly curved mesally in dorsal or ventral view and slightly curved dorsally in lateral view, extending slightly beyond apex of median lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8A9D7BDCADF8C5FB82F8B8" blockId="6.[151,1437,1311,2019]" box="[201,1104,1887,1911]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8A9D7BDCADF8C5FECFF8B8" box="[201,285,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Female</emphasis>
. Sternites VII and VIII simple. Other characters similar to those of male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
