<subSubSection id="25F9656DFF8A9D7ADCADF832FDCFFF38" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8A9D7ADCADF832FDCFFF38" blockId="6.[151,1437,1311,2019]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,319]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8A9D7BDCADF832FEEFF80F" bold="true" box="[201,317,1960,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
Habitus of the new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="AAE34D65FF8A9D7BDF64F833FB88F870" authority="Watanabe &amp; Xiao" authorityName="Watanabe &amp; Xiao" box="[768,1114,1959,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8A9D7BDF64F833FC5FF870" box="[768,909,1960,1984]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">N. giganteus</emphasis>
Watanabe &amp; Xiao
</taxonomicName>
from Yunnan. 
<taxonomicName id="AAE34D65FF8A9D7BD966F833FA4EF870" box="[1282,1436,1959,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalobus">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8A9D7BD966F833FAC7F80F" box="[1282,1301,1961,1984]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8A9D7BD947F83DFA4EF870" box="[1315,1436,1959,1983]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">megalobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the prosternum with the median carina extending to the anterior border and aedeagus with the dorso-lateral apophysis extending slightly beyond apex of the median lobe. 
<taxonomicName id="AAE34D65FF8B9D7ADF3FFF03FBF4FF7F" box="[859,1062,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8B9D7ADF3FFF03FBF4FF7F" box="[859,1062,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Nazeris giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the median prosternal carina lacking behind anterior margin and aedeagus with the dorso-lateral apophysis shorter than the median lobe (
<bibRefCitation id="09724B17FF8B9D7ADCFAFF45FDDDFF38" author="Watanabe" box="[158,527,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" refString="Watanabe, Y. &amp; Xiao, N. N. (1997) Four new Nazeris (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) from Yunnan Province, Southwest China. Edaphologia, 58, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1997">
Watanabe &amp; Xiao 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8B9D7ADD0BFF45FE79FF38" box="[367,427,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" value="1997.0">1997</number>
: 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8B9D7ADDD2FF45FE14FF38" box="[438,454,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" value="5.0">5</number>
, fig. 
<number id="DB2B24C1FF8B9D7ADD9BFF45FDDDFF38" box="[511,527,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" value="6.0">6</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="25F9656DFF8B9D7ADCADFE9EFE19FEF0" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6D5C36E6FF8B9D7ADCADFE9EFE19FEF0" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5F97EAF4FF8B9D7ADCADFE9EFE9DFED3" bold="true" box="[201,335,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is composed of the words &quot;meg&quot; and &quot;lob&quot;, in allusion to the robust dorso-lateral apophysis of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
